## 🧪 Testing Rules

### What Every Test Must Have
1. **Numerical assertion**: `REQUIRE(actual == Approx(expected).margin(tolerance))`
2. **At least 2 parameter sets** (not just one hardcoded case)
3. **At least one edge case** (dry cells, zero flux, NODATA)
4. **Memory safety check**: pass under `-fsanitize=address`

### Default Numerical Tolerances
- Matrix/RHS coefficient regression: max absolute difference < `1e-9`
- One-step deterministic solver regression: L2 or max error < `1e-8`
- Full benchmark time series against legacy output: L2 < `1e-6`
- MPI rank-count equivalence for the same executable/backend: L2 < `1e-10`
- Do not require `1e-12` unless comparing a closed-form scalar expression independent of solver ordering.

### Test Labels (CTest)
- `cpu`: runs on CPU (default)
- `gpu`: requires GPU + Kokkos-aware PETSc (skipped on macOS)
- `mpi`: requires MPI (tests parallelism)
- `regression`: regression test against reference solution
- `integration`: multi-module integration test

### Benchmark Gates (BLOCKING)
- Phase N+1 CANNOT start until Phase N's benchmark gate passes
- b1-sw (L2 < 1e-6 vs legacy) → gate for SWE completion
- b2-gw (L2 < 1e-2 vs Warrick 9-point reference) → gate for RE completion
- b3-b6 → flexible validation with trend checking (see Appendix B)

---

## 🚫 FORBIDDEN Patterns (Will Fail Code Review)

| Pattern | Why Forbidden | Correct Alternative |
|---------|---------------|---------------------|
| `DMDA` / `DMDACreate*` / `DMCreateMatrix` | Welds physics to PETSc; blocks Trilinos/Ginkgo swap | Model-owned `DomainDecomposition`; `MatMPIAIJ` + explicit preallocation inside the PETSc backend |
| `Mat`/`Vec`/`KSP`/`DM`/`Tpetra::*` in physics code | Couples physics to a solver library | `LinearSolver` / `SparseSystem` interface |
| `MatCreateSeqAIJ` / `MatCreateSeqBAIJ` | Creates separate sequential matrix path | `MatMPIAIJ` via the PETSc backend; serial = one rank |
| `PETSC_COMM_SELF` in solver code | Locks solver to one rank | `PETSC_COMM_WORLD`; select one-rank or MPI at runtime |
| Hand-rolled / custom Krylov solver | Bypasses the sanctioned backend | `LinearSolver` interface (PETSc KSP default) |
| `new[]` / `delete[]` | Manual memory management, leak-prone | `Kokkos::View` |
| `std::vector<real>` for state | Not GPU-compatible, no dual-space | `Kokkos::View<real*>` |
| `std::cout` in Kokkos lambda | Not GPU-callable | `Kokkos::printf` (device) or host-side output |
| Hard-coded grid size | Not general | Read from YAML / `Grid` object |
| `return 0;` in non-main | Stub implementation | Real implementation or ASK |
| `TODO` / `FIXME` in src/ | Incomplete code | Fix it or create a task |

