## 📌 Phase 1 Status — COMPLETE (build system + core infra)

P1 (reproducible CMake build, core types, driver skeleton, code-quality gates) is done.
Clean configure+build (zero warnings), 3/3 ctest, P1→P2 gate OPEN. Carry-forward facts:

- **Compiler**: `g++-15`/`gcc-15`, **C++20** (matches the local Kokkos 5.1.1 build,
  `Kokkos_CXX_STANDARD=20`, devices `OpenMP;Serial`).
- **Dependency discovery** (all from `/Users/zhili/Codes/local`): MPI via `find_package(MPI)`
  **pinned to local MPICH** wrappers (`bin/mpicxx`, `bin/mpicc`, `bin/mpiexec`); PETSc via
  `cmake/FindPETSc.cmake` (pkg-config wrapper → `PETSc::PETSc`); Kokkos/yaml-cpp via CMake
  config; HDF5 via `HDF5_ROOT` as **C** component only (`COMPONENTS C`, not `CXX`).
- **MPI runs MUST use the local MPICH `mpiexec`** (`/Users/zhili/Codes/local/bin/mpiexec`,
  wired into CMake as `MPIEXEC_EXECUTABLE`). Homebrew's `mpiexec` runs the MPICH-linked
  binary as size-1 singletons.
- **PETSc matrix typing**: default `aij` → `seqaij` on 1 rank, `mpiaij` on N ranks; the
  solver path always selects `MATMPIAIJ` explicitly (serial = one-rank MPIAIJ). Never
  `MatCreateSeqAIJ`.
- **Public headers** live under `include/frehg2/...` (`core/define.hpp`, `core/types.hpp`).
  `real = double`; Kokkos View aliases (`RealArr*`/`IntArr*` + `*Host`); `index_t = int32`.
- **Tests**: vendored minimal Catch2-style harness `tests/frehg2_test.hpp` (no Catch2/GTest
  installed). Keep test sources Catch2-API-compatible. CQ1 negative test compiles a bad
  fixture under strict flags with `WILL_FAIL`. CQ6 `check_no_seqaij` target greps `src/`.
- **Framework lifecycle** (`src/driver/main.cpp`): init Kokkos → MPI → PETSc; finalize
  PETSc → Kokkos → MPI. `--help`/`--version` handled before any init.

