## 📌 Phase 2 + 2B Status — COMPLETE (data structures, MPI, backend-agnostic solver)

P2 (core data structures, MPI, model-owned decomposition, backend-agnostic solver layer)
and P2B (solver-backend evaluation criteria + bake-off harness) are done. Clean
zero-warning build; **19/19 ctest pass** (13 serial + 6 multi-rank); both seam checks
pass; P2→P3 and P2B→P3 gates OPEN. Carry-forward facts:

- **Indexing**: Frehg2 uses **halo-padded flat** storage (one ghost on each horizontal
  side; z has NO halo). `src/core/Grid.hpp`: `getIndex(i,j,k)=(i+1)+(j+1)*(nx+2)+k*(nx+2)*(ny+2)`.
  Legacy interior ordering is bridged ONLY by `include/frehg2/core/LegacyIndexAdapter.hpp`
  (use it for any legacy/reference comparison; never compare raw indices).
- **No PETSc `DMDA`**. The model owns its layout via `src/linear/DomainDecomposition.hpp`
  (`DecompBase` → `Decomp2D` 5-pt / `Decomp3D` 7-pt; z is on-rank, no MPI in z) and its
  halo exchange via `src/core/MpiComm.hpp` (hand-written `MPI_Sendrecv`). Global row
  numbering is contiguous within a rank, rank-major (matches PETSc Vec/Mat layout exactly).
- **Solver seam**: physics targets only `include/frehg2/linear/{SparseSystem,LinearSolver,
  SolverConfig}.hpp` (COO emit via `addRow`/`addCOO`). PETSc types appear ONLY in
  `src/linear/backends/` (`PetscLinearSolver`, `KokkosPetscBridge`). Enforced by CMake
  targets `check_solver_seam` (no `MatSetValues` outside the bridge; no `Mat/Vec/KSP/DM/
  Tpetra` in `src/{swe,re,solute,coupling}`) and `check_no_seqaij`.
- **Library layering**: `frehg2_core` (Kokkos+MPI) ← `frehg2_decomp` (NO PETSc; proven by
  `test_decomp_no_petsc`) ← `frehg2_petsc_backend` (the only PETSc-linked lib). Link the
  backend alone (it pulls the rest transitively) to avoid duplicate-library link warnings.
- **PetscLinearSolver** builds `MATMPIAIJ` (or `MATAIJKOKKOS` with `FREHG2_USE_GPU_MAT`),
  preallocated from `DomainDecomposition::ownedRowStencil`; RHS/solution bridge via
  `VecGetArray` (host). Serial = one-rank MPIAIJ + PETSc KSP (no custom Krylov).
- **Local PETSc lacks a direct LU for `mpiaij`** (no MUMPS/SuperLU). Deterministic serial
  bring-up uses `cg + jacobi` at tight `rtol`; `pc_type lu` works unchanged via
  `SolverConfig` on a MUMPS-enabled (e.g. Linux) build.
- **AddressSanitizer unavailable** (Homebrew gcc-15 has no `libasan` on Darwin; Valgrind
  unavailable on Apple Silicon). Memory safety is structural: `src/` uses only
  `Kokkos::View` + PETSc RAII destructors; no raw `new`/`delete`/`malloc`.
- **Bake-off** (`tools/solver_bakeoff.cpp`, P2B) runs every locally-available backend
  through the `LinearSolver` interface; unbuilt backends are skipped with a logged reason.
  Measured bake-off on real SWE/RE systems is deferred to after P4c/P5.

