## 📌 Phase 3 Status — COMPLETE (I/O layer: config, HDF5, raster, time series, checkpoints)

P3 is done and the **P3→P4 gate has PASSED**. Clean zero-warning build; **30/30 ctest pass**
(21 cpu + 9 mpi, serial and `mpiexec -n 2`), including the python/h5py interop check and both
seam checks. Library: `frehg2_io` (`Frehg2::io`) links `Frehg2::core` + yaml-cpp + HDF5 C +
MPI. Carry-forward facts:

- **Config** (`src/io/Config.{hpp,cpp}`): yaml-cpp wrapper with dotted paths
  (`time.t_end`), `get`/`getOr`/`has`/`indexedCount`, relative-path resolution, and schema
  validation (modules present; `time.{t_end,dt}` numeric; `domain.{nx,ny,nz}` positive).
  Missing keys throw with the key + file; nothing is silently defaulted. Traversal uses a
  **const recursive descent** — never `node = node[key]` (that aliasing assignment mutates
  the yaml-cpp tree).
- **OutputWriter seam** (`include/frehg2/io/OutputWriter.hpp`): solvers/Orchestrator hold an
  `OutputWriter&` and call `makeOutputWriter(format,...)`; never a concrete HDF5 type. Fields
  are passed as **owned cells (no halo) + a global-index map (`IoLayout`)**: surface idx
  `gi+gj*nx`, subsurface `gi+gj*nx+k*nx*ny`. Any decomposition reassembles to the same global
  field on disk.
- **io_mode** (`output.io_mode`, default `serial_gather`): resolves parallel-write vs.
  compression per `docs/io_strategy.md` — `serial_gather` (rank0 gather, gzip-6),
  `parallel_collective` (shared file, collective MPI-IO, uncompressed),
  `file_per_rank` (per-file gzip + index reassembly). Mode is recorded in metadata.
- **Provenance (required in every file)**: `/simulation/metadata` carries `git_sha`,
  `git_dirty`, `config_sha256`, `build_type`, `compiler`, `kokkos_backend`, `solver_backend`,
  `mpi_ranks`, `io_mode`; each field dataset has a `units` attr. Build facts come from the
  CMake-generated `frehg2/io/build_info.hpp` (`cmake/build_info.hpp.in`); `config_sha256` is a
  vendored SHA-256 (`src/io/Sha256.*`, NIST-vector tested) of the resolved YAML.
- **Checkpoints** (`Hdf5Writer::writeCheckpoint`/`Hdf5Reader::readCheckpoint`, structs in
  `include/frehg2/io/Checkpoint.hpp`): **separate file per set**, atomic commit
  temp → `H5Fflush` → `fsync` → `rename(2)`, prune to `time.max_checkpoints`. Each stores its
  own `config_sha256`/`git_sha`; read reports `config_matches`. Time-loop integration is P7.
- **HDF5 = C API** (`H5Cpp.h` not present locally). Every HDF5 id is RAII-wrapped by
  `h5::Guard` (`src/io/Hdf5Support.*`). HDF5 here is parallel-enabled (`H5_HAVE_PARALLEL`),
  so all three io_modes are exercised. XDMF `.xmf` sidecar emitted on `close()` (rank 0).
- **h5py interop**: `tests/io/check_h5py.py` (`test_hdf5_h5py`) is auto-registered when
  python3 + h5py are importable (h5py 3.11 present locally).
- ASan still unavailable on this toolchain; `frehg2_io` adds no manual memory management
  (RAII guards + `Kokkos::View` + std containers only).

