## 📌 Phase 7 Status — COMPLETE (general-purpose Orchestrator; P7→P8 gate PASSED)

P7 is the **single general-purpose production driver**. `Orchestrator` is now the ONLY path
from `main()` to physics; benchmark-specific driver logic is gone. Clean zero-warning
`-Werror` build, **50/50 ctest green** (37 cpu incl. 8 integration + 13 mpi), both seam
checks pass. The `frehg2` binary runs a single schema-2.0 YAML end-to-end on 1 and 2 ranks
(gathered HDF5 + XDMF + `simulation_summary.txt`).

Implemented (all in `src/driver/`, library `frehg2_orchestrator` = `Frehg2::orchestrator`):
- `Orchestrator.{hpp,cpp}` — `initialize/step/run/restart`. Builds grid/MPI/solvers/IO from
  YAML; enables `SweSolver`/`ReSolver` per `modules.*` (+ `simulation.mode` warning/throw on
  mismatch); only enabled solvers are instantiated (`swe()`/`re()` are null otherwise).
- `main.cpp` rewritten to `Config::fromFile → Orchestrator::initialize → run()` (or
  `restart(file,time)` with `--restart`/`--restart-time`).
- **Seam-clean linear solver**: `include/frehg2/linear/LinearSolverFactory.hpp` +
  `src/linear/backends/LinearSolverFactory.cpp` (`makeLinearSolver`) so the Orchestrator gets
  a `LinearSolver` with **no PETSc include** in `src/driver`.
- **Coupled time-stepping (P7.3)**: fixed SW `dt`, adaptive GW substeps catch up to SW time
  (`while gw_time < t_new: re_->advanceStep()`); per-SW-step exchange via the new granular
  `Coupling::exchange()` (compute→limit→apply, no solver advance).

Carry-forward facts:
- **Bit-exact restart (P7.4)** needs the FULL halo-padded solver state, not just eta/u/v/wc:
  `CheckpointState`/`RestartState` gained an `extra` map; `SweFields`/`GwFields` expose
  `namedViews()` (name→`RealArr1DHost*`); `writeCheckpointNow` dumps every field, `restart`
  restores them. GW adaptive dt is re-primed via `ReSolver::primeAdaptiveDt(dt)` (sets both
  `params_.dt` and `dtn_`). Restart is **serial-only** (throws on >1 rank). Parity:
  continuous-vs-restarted L2 < 1e-10 for both b1-sw and b2-gw.
- **Orchestrator parity (P7.1)**: `tests/integration/test_orchestrator_parity.cpp` proves the
  Orchestrator reproduces the P4 `b1-sw` and P5 `b2-gw` direct-call paths to **L2 < 1e-10**.
- **`timeKey` fix (in `src/io/Hdf5Writer.cpp`)**: whole-second snapshot times keep their plain
  integer dataset name ("0","1800", backward-compatible with P3 tests); **sub-second times now
  get a lossless trimmed-decimal name** ("0.3", "0.0001") so two distinct snapshots/checkpoints
  no longer collide (`surf_times_`/`subs_times_` are now `map<field, map<time,key>>`; XDMF uses
  the stored key). Tests that build checkpoint filenames must mirror this (see `ckptKey` in
  `test_restart.cpp`).
- **ESRI raster DEM bathymetry (P7.2.2 partial)**: `domain.bathymetry.format: raster|auto|list`
  (auto ⇒ `.asc` is a raster) loads a DEM via `AsciiRaster`; raster rows are north-first
  (row 0 ↔ largest gj). A raster DEM and an equivalent plain list agree to **L2 = 0**.
- **DEFERRED (user-authorized 2026-06-27)**: true NODATA **inactive-cell masking** (no-flux
  walls / assembly skip) → **P12** (domain-masking / polygon-BC). The legacy-exact P4/P5
  solvers have no inactive-cell concept; NODATA cells are filled with the minimum valid
  elevation and stay active, with a warning. Do NOT claim irregular-domain masking until P12.
- On-node Kokkos/GPU for the driver stays the global P9/P10 pass (DP3).

