## 📌 Phase 13 Status — COMPLETE (non-uniform soil; P13 → P14 gate PASSED)

P13 adds spatially variable soil (Ksat / porosity / VG α,n / residual). Clean `-Werror` build;
**66/66 ctest** (incl. 4 new soil tests); both seam checks pass; b1-sw/b2-gw bit-identical.
Carry-forward facts:

- **Module layout**: new `src/soil/` lib `Frehg2::soil` (`SoilMap.{hpp,cpp}` = class table +
  per-cell class-index raster + CSV/uniform load; `SoilConfig.{hpp,cpp}` = `parseSoilClasses`).
  **No separate `KField` class** — the K assembly stays in `ReSolver`. `SoilParams` promoted to
  the public header `include/frehg2/re/SoilParams.hpp` to break a re↔soil include cycle. Lib DAG:
  `core ← soil(→io) ← re ← orchestrator`.
- **Per-cell soil**: `ReSolver::soilAt(i,j[,k])` returns the SoilMap class (per-column at P13;
  **fully per-cell (i,j,k) as of P23**), or uniform `params_.soil` when no map (clamped indices so
  ghost-neighbor face lookups resolve to the adjacent interior cell). EVERY per-cell constitutive use
  (computeKFace, storage Gct/Grhs, room, retention/realloc/clamp, capacity, adaptive-dt, Darcy flux,
  IC head) reads `soilAt`. **K-face = `0.5*(K(own)+K(neighbor))`** (own vs +x/+y/+z neighbor cell
  soil). **No map ⇒ bit-identical P5** (b2-gw, RE MPI np2/np4, orchestrator
  parity all green).
- **Schema** (reuses existing keys, NOT plan's `map_file`/`classes_file`): `soil.types` IS the
  ordered class list (id == position); `soil.map: {from_file, file, format}` (list `gi+gj*nx` or
  ESRI `.asc`, same orientation as bathymetry). Per-class overrides of `specific_storage`/
  `use_vg`/`use_mvg`/`air_entry_value`; else default to global `groundwater.*`.
- **Wiring**: `Orchestrator::buildSoilMap` (called from `buildGroundwater`, AFTER `setParams`,
  BEFORE `initializeUniformColumn`) is a **no-op unless `soil.map.from_file`**; reads the global
  class raster, slices each rank's owned block, validates ids, `re_->setSoilMap`. Soil is static
  (built once, no per-step assembly).
- **Gate DEVIATION (user-authorized 2026-06-28)**: the plan's `b4-govindaraju` gate is INVALID —
  the registered b4 is a **SERGHEI overland-flow (SWE) benchmark** (DEM + rainfall + Chezy,
  `InfModel:none`, no soil/GW, `gate: review`, `tolerance: null`); the registry overrides plan
  prose. P13 is gated instead by `tests/soil/test_nonuniform_soil.cpp` (2-class laterally-decoupled
  box: each class column reproduces its per-class uniform run to **6.1e-16**; inter-class margin
  **4.3e-3** > 1e-3) + `tests/integration/test_soil_orchestrator.cpp` (full `soil.map` path:
  map col-0 == uniform col-0 to 1.5e-13; col-0 vs col-1 differ 2.4e-3). Unit tests:
  `test_soil_map` (incl. 1e6-row CSV), `test_yaml_soil` (2/4/16 classes).

