## 📌 Phase 16 Status — COMPLETE (solute production integration; P16 → P9 gate PASSED)

P16 wires the standalone P8 `SoluteStepper` into the production `Orchestrator` under
`solute.enabled: true` (operator splitting: one solute pass AFTER each flow step). Clean
`-Werror` build; **75/75 ctest** (2 new integration tests); both seam checks pass; b1-sw/b2-gw
orchestrator parity unchanged. Carry-forward facts:

- **`Orchestrator::buildSolute`** (called from `initialize` after `buildPolygons`) is a NO-OP
  unless `solute.enabled` — which is **authoritative and overrides `modules.solute`**. When on,
  it allocates the canonical conc storage (P2 `State`/`GwState`, the `conc` members), the
  `SoluteStepper`, and **dedicated solute diffusion `LinearSolver` backends** (separate KSP/matrix
  from SWE/RE; built only when `solute.diffusion_scheme: implicit` and `solute.D > 0`). Solute
  owns no PETSc type (diffusion goes through the LinearSolver seam); `frehg2_orchestrator` links
  `Frehg2::solute`.
- **`Orchestrator::applySolute`** runs inside `step()` AFTER the flow advance (all three branches:
  coupled, SW-only, GW-only). It snapshots the **start-of-step** flow (surface depth = post-step
  depth minus the rain the SWE just added in `evaprain`), applies the **rainfall mixing in the
  Orchestrator** (NOT the stepper) so it can mirror the SWE's global y+ row exclusion exactly
  (`globalJ != gny-1`) — this makes the rain solute exactly balance the rain water so
  `Sum(C*depth)` is conserved — then calls the stepper with `rain=0` (it still does infiltration
  mixing / decay / advection / diffusion). Solute substeps = `solute.substeps` (default 1, solute
  dt = flow dt / substeps).
- **CFL limiter**: a refused (advective CFL > `solute.cfl_max`) substep triggers a retry with
  progressively finer substepping (cap 4096), warning once. The **flow `dt` is never changed**
  (deviates from the plan's "halve flow dt" to preserve SWE legacy parity).
- **Async + solute**: `runLoop` forces the sequential loop when `solute_` is active (the P11
  async pipeline lags the GW window, which has no defined transport semantics).
- **Output**: `concentration` surface + subsurface fields appended to every snapshot (`kg/m^3`).
- **Monitors**: `MonitorWriter::writeRow` gained optional `surf_conc`/`subs_conc` host views (owned
  by the Orchestrator, not the solvers) backing the **`C`/`conc`/`concentration`** probe field.
- **Checkpoint/restart**: conc stored in checkpoint `extra` (`solute_sw_conc`/`solute_gw_conc`)
  plus the documented `checkpoint/solute/C`; `has_solute` set; restored in `loadCheckpointState`
  (serial-only, like all restart). Continuous-vs-restarted conc L2 < 1e-12.
- **Mass balance** (`simulation_summary.txt`, only when solute on): `solute_initial_mass`,
  `solute_final_mass`, `solute_added_by_rain`, `solute_decay_loss`, `solute_relative_mass_error`.
  `computeSoluteMass = Sum(C*depth*area)` (surface) + `Sum(C*wc*vol)` (subsurface), MPI-reduced.
- **Gate DEVIATIONS (recorded in `INTEGRATED_PLAN.md` P16 note)**: (1) the strict 1e-9 mass gate
  (`test_solute_in_orchestrator`) uses an **`nx=1` closed column with a dry y+ wall** so the wet
  region is quiescent — the legacy SWE position-based BCs are tuned for the closed b1-sw column,
  a generic `nx>1` box is not closed in x, and the **P8 advection conserves CELL-SUM of C, not
  depth-weighted mass**, so mass-vs-transport parity is exact only in a quiescent/uniform-depth
  field. `test_solute_restart` uses a flat rained basin with REAL flow to exercise full transport,
  gated by L2<1e-12 reproducibility. (2) SW↔GW solute exchange is **WIRED** (P16-completion,
  2026-07-01): the coupling exports its per-column limited flux (`Coupling::exchange(..., q_out)`)
  and the Orchestrator moves dissolved mass with exactly that water
  (`applyCouplingSoluteExchange` → `applyInterfaceExchange`), co-located with the water exchange so
  the donor concentration and post-exchange heights are exact ⇒ total solute mass conserved to
  machine precision (gates `test_solute_exchange` rel-err 1e-16, `test_source_sink`). The old
  non-conservative stepper `qss`/`applyInfiltrationMixing` path (and `SoluteFlow::qss`) were
  removed. Solute IC (`initial_conditions.solute.{surface,subsurface}`) is now applied too (it was
  parsed-but-unwired). (3) On-node Kokkos/GPU for the solute path stays the global P9/P10 pass (DP3).

## 📌 Phase 9 Status — COMPLETE (on-node Kokkos local loops; P9 → P10 gate PASSED)

P9 is the **single, numerical-free on-node parallelization pass** (DP3): every per-cell loop in
`src/{swe,re,solute,coupling,driver}` was converted to Kokkos through the new wrappers, with
bit-identical CPU/OpenMP results as the gate. Clean `-Werror` build; **76/77 ctest green** (1 gpu
stub DISABLED locally); both seam checks pass; all parity gates hold. Carry-forward facts:

- **Wrappers** (`include/frehg2/core/ParallelFor.hpp`): `parallelForRange(name,n,f)` (flat),
  `parallelForSurface(name,nx,ny,f)` (2-D `MDRangePolicy<Rank<2>>`), `parallelForVolume(name,nx,ny,
  nz,f)` (3-D). `LoopExec = Kokkos::DefaultHostExecutionSpace` (**OpenMP** here; Serial fallback);
  the identical kernel bodies become device kernels on a Kokkos-CUDA build (P10). Reductions use
  `Kokkos::parallel_reduce` with `Kokkos::Max`/`Kokkos::Min` (order-independent ⇒ bit-identical) for
  CFL / max-conc / Courant; **sums** use `parallel_reduce` only for **diagnostics** (solute mass).
- **Full per-loop classification: `docs/local_loops_audit.md`** (authoritative). Loops deliberately
  kept **sequential** (and why): Gauss–Seidel sweep dependencies — `ReSolver::reallocateWaterContent`
  (reads neighbor `wc` that the same sweep overwrites; this IS the b2-gw element-wise parity) and the
  `bot1d` prefix sum; neighbor-write scatter — the `SweSolver::updateVelocity` limiter; boundary/ghost
  edge fills; **COO assembly** (solver seam — PETSc staging stays in the backend, only the solution
  **unpack** is parallel); and sums whose bit-identity a test asserts (`Coupling::exchange` total).
- **Device-callable helpers**: `VanGenuchten` (all static methods), `darcyFluxZ`, and solute
  `minmod`/`faceValue` are `KOKKOS_INLINE_FUNCTION` with **`std::` math → `Kokkos::` math**
  (`pow/fabs/exp/log/sqrt/max/min`). Member helpers called from lambdas via a captured
  `const Solver* self`; `Grid` captured by value (its indexers are `KOKKOS_INLINE_FUNCTION`); Views
  and scalars captured by value. `continue` in serial loops becomes `return` inside the lambda.
- **Gate**: `b0-lake`, `b1-sw` serial + MPI np2/np4, **`b2-gw` legacy dt replay** (strict
  element-wise parity, ~186 s), RE MPI np2/np4, orchestrator parity & restart (all L2 < 1e-10) —
  unchanged after conversion. New `tests/core/test_parallel_for.cpp` proves the wrappers reproduce
  serial element-wise writes and that `Max`/`Min` equal the serial scan bit-for-bit, plus the
  `continue→return` skip equivalence. GPU host/device equivalence (`test_parallel_for_gpu`, label
  `gpu`) is registered **DISABLED** (no CUDA locally), deferred to P10 Linux/NVIDIA validation.

## 📌 Phase 10 Status — COMPLETE (GPU backend behind compile guards; P10 → P18 gate PASSED)

P10 adds the **GPU-capable Kokkos→PETSc backend** behind compile guards. The macOS OpenMP build is
**unchanged and bit-identical to P9**; real CUDA execution is the deferred Linux/NVIDIA validation
(`docs/gpu_validation_policy.md`). Clean `-Werror` build; **76/76 ctest green** (4 `gpu` tests
DISABLED/skipped); `check_no_seqaij` + `check_solver_seam` + new `check_gpu_coo_assembly` pass.
Carry-forward facts:

- **Assembly-path selector**: `src/linear/backends/GpuAssembly.hpp` defines `FREHG2_GPU_ASSEMBLY`
  (1 iff `KOKKOS_ENABLE_CUDA|HIP|SYCL`). On macOS it is **0** ⇒ the host-staged **Option A**
  (`MatSetValues` on HostSpace, the P9-validated path) is active and every device path is compiled
  out. The macro is derived from the Kokkos device macros — no runtime switch.
- **Option B (GPU-native)**: `KokkosPetscBridgeDevice.cpp` (its own TU; empty on non-GPU) does
  `MatSetPreallocationCOO` (`setPreallocationCOODevice`, indices host-staged once) +
  `MatSetValuesCOO` (`assembleCOODevice`, device value pointer, **no host staging**).
  `PetscSparseSystem::addCOO` dispatches to it under the guard, caching the COO pattern on the
  first call (`coo_preallocated_`). `addRow` keeps the host path (Option A) on all builds.
- **Vec bridge**: `PetscSparseSystem::setRhs`/`getSolution` keep RHS/solution **device-resident** on
  GPU via `VecGetArrayAndMemType`/`VecGetArrayReadAndMemType` + device↔device `Kokkos::deep_copy`
  (subview to `n_local_`); the host element loop stays on CPU.
- **GPU async (Task 10.3.7)**: `src/linear/backends/PetscSubcommSplit.{hpp,cpp}` — guarded
  `AsyncSolverGroups`: `PetscSubcomm` 2-way split {Surface, Groundwater} + per-domain
  stream-backed `DeviceExec` (via `Kokkos::Experimental::partition_space`) + `fenceAll()` barrier.
  Empty TU on non-GPU; the **CPU/OpenMP async pipeline (P11) remains the numerical reference**.
  Design: `docs/research_notes/async_gpu.md`.
- **Static check**: `check_gpu_coo_assembly` (CMake target) asserts the device assembly TU uses
  `MatSetValuesCOO` only (grep: no `MatSetValues(`; must contain `MatSetValuesCOO`).
- **GPU tests** (`tests/gpu/`, label `gpu`, **DISABLED** when `FREHG2_ENABLE_CUDA=OFF`):
  `test_b1_sw_gpu` (b1 runner vs legacy reference), `test_b2_gw_gpu` (Orchestrator-vs-direct RE),
  `test_async_coupling_gpu` (coupled sync-vs-async, 1e-10). Bodies guarded by `FREHG2_GPU_ASSEMBLY`
  so they compile to a skip locally; they link the same libs as the CPU gates.
- **Build switch**: `cmake -DFREHG2_ENABLE_CUDA=ON` (Linux/NVIDIA only — **FATAL on macOS**) adds
  `FREHG2_ENABLE_CUDA=1` and un-disables the gpu tests; the assembly path still keys on the Kokkos
  device macros (so a Kokkos-CUDA + Kokkos-aware PETSc toolchain is what actually flips Option B on).
- **Multi-GPU policy**: `docs/research_notes/single_rank_multi_gpu.md` — multi-GPU = more MPI ranks
  (one GPU per rank, via the existing `DomainDecomposition`); single-rank multi-GPU is a P22 research
  item, not implemented.

## 📌 Phase 17 Status — COMPLETE (production YAML schema v2 + migration; P17 → P18 gate PASSED)

P17 publishes the P0-frozen schema as the externally documented **v2 schema** and adds the
