  (walks `benchmarks/{b1-sw,b2-gw,b0-lake}.yaml`; curated units/descriptions). Freshness CTest
  `test_yaml_schema_doc_fresh` (`gen_yaml_schema_doc.py --check`, registered only if PyYAML
  present). Appendix A of the plan is a quick summary; this doc is the full reference.
- **DEVIATION (b3–b6)**: only the benchmarks with Frehg2 v2 configs (**b0/b1/b2**) are migrated
  here. **b3–b6 are SERGHEI cases whose Frehg2 v2 conversion is created in P18** — consistent
  with `benchmarks/reference_registry.yaml` (authoritative; "reference finalized at P18/P21").
  Sequence access is via `Config::root()[...]` + integer index (the dotted `get(path)` does NOT
  index sequences).

## 📌 Phase 18 Status — COMPLETE (b3–b6 benchmark ports, review-tier; P18 → P19 gate PASSED)

P18 ports the remaining four benchmarks to Frehg2 production at **review tier** (user-authorized
2026-06-30). The authoritative `benchmarks/reference_registry.yaml` gates **all four `review`,
`tolerance: null`**, and the realized solver scope does not match the plan's strict L2 premises —
b3–b5 are **SERGHEI** cases (multi-file `.input`, Chezy friction, Picard/2-D Richards), b6 is a
**legacy Frehg** coupled case (Newton `iter_solve=1` + baroclinic). Clean `-Werror` build,
**83/83 ctest pass** (4 GPU disabled), both seam checks pass. Carry-forward facts:

- **Each benchmark** has `benchmarks/<id>/<id>.yaml` (v2 schema) + copied forcing artifacts
  (`dem.asc` ESRI raster, `bath` list, `rain` series in m/s), an integration test
  `tests/integration/test_b{3,4,5,6}_*.cpp` (shared `benchmark_util.hpp`), and a doc
  `docs/benchmarks/b{3,4,5,6}-*.md` with three-tier (PASS/REVIEW/FAIL) thresholds. All 6
  benchmarks now have v2 configs (`python3 tools/run_benchmark.py --list`).
- **Review-tier tests assert real physics, not strict L2**: stability, finite/non-negative state,
  mass conservation (storage + outlet outflow ≤ rainfall delivered — no spurious creation),
  `wc∈[θr,θs]`, conservative SW↔GW exchange. Runs are **capped** via `time.max_steps` (the real
  runs are 4800–432000 s; far too long for CI).
- **b4-govindaraju** ✅ SWE overland plane (200×10 DEM); **Manning approximates SERGHEI Chezy**;
  polygon `bc_critical` outlet; **`min_depth=1e-8`** so the small per-step rain increment on the
  finely-celled plane (dx≈0.11 m) accumulates instead of being clamped to dry. (This wet/dry
  clamp — `eta=bottom` when `0<depth<min_depth` in `evaprain` — destroys sub-`min_depth` water
  every step; keep `min_depth` below the per-step rain increment for slow rain on fine grids.)
- **b5-vcatchment** ✅ SWE overland flow on the real 101×55 V-catchment DEM; **SW-only** (the
  subsurface/coupling leg is deferred — needs lateral Richards); uniform Manning (per-cell
  roughness file not applied); polygon `bc_critical` outlet. Refs are inter-model (CATHY/HGS/PF).
- **b6-kuan** ✅ coupled SW–GW on the real 1×68×10 geometry via the **PCA path** (legacy used
  Newton `iter_solve=1`, not implemented); solute/baroclinic disabled; sync coupling. Named
  **b6-kuan** (Kuan et al.), never the old wrong name.
- **b3-kirkland** ✅ **FULL 2-D port (P23 follow-up, 2026-06-30)** — was BLOCKED at P18 (RE was
  vertical-only + per-column soil). P23 (3-D lateral RE + per-cell soil) plus the new partial-width
  top fixed-flux BC now make it a genuine **2-D (50×1×30, x-z) layered infiltration** (`full_3d:
  true`, 30-layer `soil.map.layers` from `gen_soil_layers.py`, `groundwater.recharge` over the
  central columns, IC head `-500`). Still **PCA, not Picard** (policy). Result: recharge mass
  conserved 99.6%; simulated h=0/h=-400 head contours match the digitized Kirkland ref0/ref400 to
  RMS ≈ 0.25/0.29 m (3 m domain) — review-tier, gated by `tests/integration/test_b3_kirkland.cpp`
  (full t=86400 run, ~42 s). See the dedicated bullet in the Phase 23 status block below.
- **`tools/run_benchmark.py`** (P18 CI integration; full three-tier compare is P19): locates
  `benchmarks/<id>/<id>.yaml`, reads the registry gate, runs `frehg2` (optionally `--max-steps`,
  `--mpiexec`/`--np`), reports PASS/REVIEW/FAIL, records GPU as DEFERRED. `--list` shows gates +
  v2-config presence.
- **`AsciiRaster` reads the SERGHEI `dem.input` format directly** (case-insensitive
  ncols/nrows/xll*/cellsize/nodata_value); DEMs are copied as `dem.asc` and read via
  `domain.bathymetry.{from_file,file,format: raster}`. SWE `setInitialEtaPhysical` clamps
  `eta` UP to `bottom` (so a flat `init eta` below the DEM ⇒ dry start at the surface).
- Benchmark driver output dirs (`benchmarks/*/out/`) are git-ignored.

## 📌 Phase 19 Status — COMPLETE (unified three-tier validation; P19 → P20 gate PASSED)

P19 is the **single authoritative "is Frehg2 working?" harness**. `tools/run_validation.py` runs
all six benchmarks + the separate `b0-lake` well-balanced check through the production `frehg2`
driver and emits `validation_report.{md,json}` with a PASS/REVIEW/FAIL tier each. Clean `-Werror`
build, **87/87 ctest green** (3 new `validation`-labeled), both seam checks pass. Carry-forward facts:

- **Current classification** (authoritative on this code): **b1-sw PASS** (relative depth L2 = 0
  vs the committed `frehg2_np1_depth_reference.txt`), **b0-lake PASS** (`max|eta-1| ~ 2e-15 < 1e-12`),
  **b2-gw / b3-kirkland / b4-govindaraju / b5-vcatchment / b6-kuan REVIEW** (stable, finite, sound
  mass balance + trends). **Overall REVIEW** — expected: five of six are registry-`review`.
- **Tooling**: `tools/run_validation.py` (main), `tools/run_b0_lake.py` (separate 1e-12 check),
  `tools/trend_check.py` (slope-sign classify + mean/RMS/peak + opposite-direction FAIL),
  `tools/validation_thresholds.yaml` (per-benchmark `metric`/strict/loose/run/`mass_fail`),
  `tools/trend_reference.yaml`. Harness exits non-zero ONLY on a FAIL tier (safe CI gate). Needs
  `h5py` + `PyYAML`.
- **Metrics**: `legacy_l2_depth` (b1-sw, true strict gate, physics matches the P4 port) vs
  `review_physics` (b2-b6; best attainable tier is REVIEW — registry gates them `review`; FAIL only
  on crash / non-finite / opposite trend / mass blowup). `well_balanced` (b0, separate).
- **Real water mass-balance** added to `simulation_summary.txt` (driver `computeWaterVolume()` +
  rain accumulator in `swAdvanceTo`; reductions before the rank-0 write guard): `water_initial_volume`,
  `water_final_volume`, `water_rain_volume_in`, `water_polygon_{inflow,outflow,well}_volume`,
  `coupling_exchange_volume`, `surface_water_present`/`groundwater_present`. **Closable for SW-only**
  (`final == initial + rain_in + inflow - outflow`); banded `<1e-10` PASS / `<mass_fail` REVIEW /
  else FAIL. **GW-present budgets are NOT closable** (GW flux-BC inflow uninstrumented) → reported
  informationally; element-wise GW legacy parity stays in ctest `test_re_b2_gw`. SWE wet/dry
  conservation floor is ~1e-6 at rest, a few % during initial dry-bed wetting (b5 `mass_fail` tuned
  to 5e-2 for the transient).
- **CI**: `.github/workflows/validation.yml` (build → ctest → harness; FAIL blocks merge; each
  REVIEW is a `::warning`; reports uploaded). Local enforcement via ctests
  `test_validation_harness_quick`, `test_b0_lake_well_balanced`, `test_trend_check` (label
  `validation`). GPU/CUDA runner wired in comments, deferred (no GPU-only benchmark today).
- **`--quick`** caps every benchmark to `quick_max_steps` for a fast smoke; `run: full` benchmarks
  (b1-sw, needed for its L2 reference times) are uncapped (`max_steps: 0`) even in quick mode.
- Docs: `docs/validation.md` (how to run, tiers, metrics, failure modes). `tools/run_benchmark.py`
  (P18) is retained; `run_validation.py` is the P19 superset.

## 📌 Phase 21 Status — COMPLETE (perf instrumentation & tuning; P21 → P22 gate PASSED)

P21 adds **performance instrumentation and three staging/setup optimizations** on the macOS OpenMP
path. Carry-forward facts:

- **Library** `Frehg2::perf` (`include/frehg2/perf/`, `src/perf/`): `ScopedTimer` (Kokkos::Timer +
  optional Kokkos profiling regions), `PerfRecorder`, `Counters`, region enum. Wired through
  `Orchestrator`, `SweSolver`, `ReSolver` — always active, no config toggle.
- **Summary output**: `simulation_summary.txt` gains `perf_*_seconds` per region, per-step
  averages, `perf_cells_touched`, `perf_ksp_iterations`, `perf_bytes_staged`. MPI `Allreduce` SUM
  at write time. Asserted in `test_simulation_summary`.
- **Tooling**: `tools/perf_report.py` (full + `--quick` sweeps); ctests `test_perf_recorder`,
  `test_perf_report_quick` (label `perf`). Docs: `docs/perf/p21_hotspots.md`.
- **Optimizations**: (1) removed duplicate `solver_->setup()` before `solve()` in SWE/RE
  (`PetscLinearSolver::solve` already calls `setup`); (2) host-alias RHS fill in
  `assembleAndSolve` (skip mirror `deep_copy` when views are already HostSpace); (3) same for
  PETSc `setRhs`/`getSolution` CPU path + solution unpack in solvers.
- **Hot spot #1 (SW KSP)** documented and **deferred** (solver path — not a wrapper bug).
- **Deferred gates** (Linux HPC/CUDA only): MPI efficiency ≥ 0.7 at 16 ranks (21.3.5); GPU ≥ 5×
  speedup at 1M cells (21.3.6). Instrumentation ready; see `docs/gpu_validation_policy.md`.
- **Regression**: P19 validation quick run — b1-sw PASS, no FAIL tiers. **89/89 ctest green**
  (+2 perf tests; 4 gpu DISABLED).

## 📌 Phase 20 Status — COMPLETE (legacy deprecation; P20 → P21 gate PASSED)

P20 formally **deprecates and archives** the legacy `frehg` C/MPI/LASPack code. Frehg2 is the only
default build; the legacy code is **never compiled by default** and is never linked or `#include`d
by any Frehg2 target. Carry-forward facts:

- **Build flag**: root `CMakeLists.txt` `option(FREHG2_USE_LEGACY ... OFF)`. Default OFF ⇒ legacy
  not built (and it was never part of the CMake build — the active build had zero legacy refs). ON ⇒
  an opt-in `legacy_frehg` custom target that forwards to the legacy's OWN historical build system
  (`legacy/frehg/makefile`, `mpicc` + LASPack), with a loud deprecation WARNING. Configure verified
  for both OFF and ON; the legacy C binary is NOT compiled on this machine (user directive).
- **Docs**: `legacy/frehg/DEPRECATED.md` (why kept, opt-in build, replacement),
  `legacy/README.md` (archival; `legacy/benchmarks/` are READ-ONLY reference fixtures — never edit;
  regenerate only via the opt-in legacy build), `README.md` rewritten Frehg2-only with a deprecation
  banner, `docs/migration_from_legacy.md` (legacy `input` → v2 YAML via `scripts/legacy_to_yaml.py`;
  v1→v2 via `tools/migrate_yaml_v1_to_v2`; output/behaviour deltas + b3-b6 review-tier caveats).
- **CI**: `.github/workflows/validation.yml` never sets `FREHG2_USE_LEGACY`, so CI never builds
  legacy; the P19 harness is the canonical test referencing legacy outputs.
- **Git note**: the repo is NOT yet under git. No legacy SHA is hardcoded — the build-provenance
  system records `git_sha` automatically once `git init` is run (reports `unknown` until then).
- **LASPack** (`legacy/frehg/src/laspack/`) is unused by Frehg2 (PETSc backend via the
  LinearSolver/SparseSystem seam); it compiles only on the opt-in legacy path.

