## 📌 Phase 23 Status — COMPLETE (3D Richards + fully heterogeneous soil; P23 gate PASSED)

P23 promotes the Richards solver from **vertical-only** to a **full 3D predictor-corrector**
(lateral x,y Darcy flux in the corrector — the implicit head solve was already 3D) and the soil
map from **per-column (2D)** to **fully heterogeneous per-cell (3D)**, matching legacy `frehg`
(`use_full3d`) and SERGHEI. **No Picard/Newton** (still `iter_solve==0, use_corrector==1`). Clean
`-Werror` build; **90/90 ctest** (+`test_re_3d`, `test_re_3d_mpi[_np2/_np4]`; 4 gpu DISABLED); all
three seam checks pass; all prior gates bit-identical. Carry-forward facts:

- **All new 3D behavior is gated behind `groundwater.full_3d: true` (`ReParams::use_full3d`)**, so
  the vertical-only path (b2-gw legacy dt replay, P5.5e decoupled RE MPI np2/np4, orchestrator
  parity & restart) is **byte-for-byte unchanged** — verified (b2-gw 183s element-wise parity green).
- **`groundwaterFlux` (corrector)**: when `use_full3d`, computes lateral `qx=Ax·Kx·visc·Δh/dx`,
  `qy=Ay·Ky·visc·Δh/dy` (`Ax=dy·dz`, `Ay=dx·dz`, no gravity laterally), matching legacy
  `darcy_flux "x"/"y","none"` (flat). `updateWaterContent` already summed `dqx+dqy+dqz`.
- **Latent bugs fixed (were dormant because b2-gw has `Ksx=Ksy=0` and the decoupled MPI gate has
  `Kx=Ky=0`)**: (1) lateral matrix coeff now carries the face area
  (`Gxp=-Kx·dt·r·Ax/dx`, …) like legacy `*Ax[ii]*dx/dx²`; (2) the no-flux wall closure zeroes the
  **correct** boundary K-face (`Kx(nx-1)` for x+, `Kx(-1)` for x−), global-index-aware for MPI;
  (3) RHS lateral Dirichlet folding is GLOBAL-boundary-keyed (interior rank boundaries carry the
  coupling as real off-diagonals — folding there would double-count); (4) `adaptiveTimeStep` face
  areas `Ax=dy·dz`, `Ay=dx·dz` (were swapped). All bit-identical when `dx=dy` / `Kx=Ky=0`.
- **3D MPI halo** (gated behind `use_full3d && size>1`): `haloExchange3D` of `h` before
  `computeKFace`; `Kx,Ky` after; `qx,qy` after the owned `+`-faces; `wc` before
  `reallocateWaterContent`. z stays on-rank. Convention: `Kx(c)`/`qx(c)` = the **+x face** of c, so
  exchanging fills the `-x` ghost (i=−1) with the neighbor's shared `+x` face ⇒ conservative
  divergence + symmetric matrix across ranks.
- **Per-cell soil**: `SoilMap` gained `setClassIndex3D`/`classAt(i,j,k)`/`is3D()`/`nz()` (0 ⇒ 2D
  per-column, replicated across k = bit-identical P13). `ReSolver::soilAt(i,j)` → `soilAt(i,j,k)` at
  EVERY constitutive use (K-face uses own & neighbor cell soils incl. the z-face k+1 cell). Orchestrator
  `soil.map.layers` (a sequence of nz per-layer class rasters/lists, top→bottom) builds a 3D map;
  the existing 2D `soil.map.file` path is unchanged.
- **Gates** (`tests/re/test_re_3d.cpp`, `tests/re/test_re_3d_mpi.cpp`, `tests/soil/test_soil_map.cpp`):
  closed heterogeneous box **conserves total water to 6e-16** (dx≠dy); lateral conductivity changes
  the field vs the vertical-only path (>1e-7); a single-class 3D map reproduces the uniform run
  **bit-for-bit (0.0)**; a layered 2-class map differs (4.7e-4); 3D MPI np2/np4 vs np1 ≈ **6–9e-9**.
- **3D MPI tolerance is ~1e-8, NOT 1e-10 (documented deviation)**: a genuinely cross-rank-coupled
  Krylov solve (CG+Jacobi — the only deterministic option on the local PETSc, which has **no parallel
  direct LU**) is partition-dependent at the ~1e-9 parallel inner-product round-off level. The SERIAL
  run conserves to ~1e-16, so the residual is solver round-off, not a halo/assembly bug (those would
  be O(1e-2)+). Bit-level coupled-solve equivalence needs MUMPS/SuperLU_DIST (Linux build), exactly
  like the documented `pc_type lu` note. The strict 1e-10 gate still holds for the **decoupled** RE
  (P5.5e) and SWE direct paths.
- **On-node Kokkos/GPU for the 3D RE path** follows the existing P9/P13 host-only pattern (soilAt
  via `const ReSolver* self` in the lambda; SoilMap is host `std::vector`-backed); a device port of
  the soil lookup is part of the deferred RE-GPU pass (DP3 / Linux-CUDA validation).
- **Top fixed-flux GW BC + full b3-kirkland (P23 follow-up, 2026-06-30)**: the legacy
  `bctype_GW[5]==2` / `qtop` path (previously dead `ReParams::qtop`) is now implemented as a
  partial-width recharge BC. `ReSolver::setTopFluxField(per-column q)` stores `qtop` per surface
  column (`grid_.getSurfaceIndex`); `groundwaterRhs` injects it for top cells (legacy
  `groundwater.c:666-669`: `Grhs += -dt·r_rhozp(km)·V·(qtop + Kz(km)·r_rhozp·r_visczp)/dz`); the PCA
  **corrector top-face flux is overridden to `qz(km)=qtop·Az`** (legacy's commented `dqep`) so the
  non-iterative scheme conserves the prescribed recharge (Picard would re-solve to consistency; PCA
  needs the explicit flux — without it the top cell drains and head blows up to ~-66000 m). `darcyFluxZ`
  back-face uses `Kp=compute_K(h_cell)` for bc5==2 (legacy `groundwater.c:288`). All gated on bc5==2,
  so bc5==0/1 (b2-gw) is byte-identical. Wired in the Orchestrator as `groundwater.recharge: {rate,
  polygon}` (`buildRecharge`; owned columns whose centroid is inside the ring get `rate`, else 0 ⇒
  no-flux top). `b3-kirkland` is now the FULL 2-D (50×1×30 x-z) layered case (`full_3d: true`,
  30-layer `soil.map.layers`, IC head `-500`): recharge mass conserved **99.6%**, h=0/h=-400 head
  contours match the digitized Kirkland ref0/ref400 to **RMS ≈ 0.25/0.29 m** in a 3 m domain
  (review-tier). Gate: `tests/integration/test_b3_kirkland.cpp` (full t=86400 run). `gen_soil_layers.py`
  builds the 30 layer files from the legacy `soilID.input`. **Still 90/90 ctest** (b3 upgraded
  surrogate→full 2-D, same count), seam checks pass, b2-gw 177s parity unchanged.

## 🚀 Quick Reference

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Migrate v1→v2 YAML | `./build/tools/migrate_yaml_v1_to_v2 in.yaml out.yaml` |
| Regenerate schema doc | `python3 tools/gen_yaml_schema_doc.py` (`--check` to verify freshness) |
| Configure | `cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=g++-15 -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=gcc-15 -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release` |
| Build | `cmake --build build -j4` |
| Run all tests | `ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure` |
| Run one test | `ctest --test-dir build -R test_name --output-on-failure` |
| Run multi-rank | `/Users/zhili/Codes/local/bin/mpiexec -n 2 ./build/frehg2 config.yaml` (local MPICH) |
| Run benchmark | `python scripts/run_benchmarks.py b1-sw` |
| Unified validation | `python tools/run_validation.py --bin build/frehg2 --out build/validation` |
| Performance report | `python tools/perf_report.py --bin build/frehg2 --out build/perf` |
| Perf report (CI smoke) | `python tools/perf_report.py --quick` |
| Validation (fast CI smoke) | `python tools/run_validation.py --quick` |
| Lake-at-rest check | `python tools/run_b0_lake.py --bin build/frehg2` |
| Memory check | ASan unavailable locally (Homebrew gcc on Darwin has no `libasan`); run on a Linux validation build: `cmake -S . -B build-asan -DCMAKE_CXX_FLAGS="-fsanitize=address" && cmake --build build-asan && ctest --test-dir build-asan` |
| Solver bake-off | `./build/tools/solver_bakeoff --nx 64 --ny 64 --nz 16 --ksp cg --pc gamg` (or via local MPICH `mpiexec -n N`) |
| Seam checks | `cmake --build build --target check_no_seqaij check_solver_seam check_gpu_coo_assembly` |
| Legacy (archival, opt-in) | `cmake -S . -B build-legacy -DFREHG2_USE_LEGACY=ON && cmake --build build-legacy --target legacy_frehg` |
| GPU build (Linux/NVIDIA only) | `cmake -S . -B build-cuda -DFREHG2_ENABLE_CUDA=ON` (FATAL on macOS); runs `gpu`-labeled tests |
| Check anti-patterns | `grep -rn 'MatCreateSeqAIJ\|PETSC_COMM_SELF\|DMDA\|DMCreateMatrix' src/` |
| Check solver leak into physics | `grep -rn 'Mat \|Vec \|KSP \|DM \|Tpetra' src/swe src/re src/solute src/coupling` (must be empty) |

